cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing and dialog systems. The use of neural networks and pre-training of word embeddings suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of an autoencoder for one-class classification suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the focus on improving the accuracy of out-of-domain sentence detection suggests that it could also belong to cs.SD (Software Engineering).
